===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Uncertain. There are some hypotheses:
* Xu Zhongshu: Bottom half of {{zh-l|*冓}}, {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of a fish, then drawn in a similar way to 丙 (perhaps a fish tail). See {{zh-l|*魚}} and {{zh-l|*丙}}<ref name="漢語多功能字庫">[https://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word=再 漢語多功能字庫 - 字頭「再」]</ref>
* Shizuka Shirakawa：{{liushu|p}} of tools used for weaving ropes.<ref name="漢語多功能字庫"/>
* Ji Xusheng: {{Han compound|ls=ic|魚|二|t1=fish|t2=two}} – to catch two fish at once ([[kill two birds with one stone]]).<ref name="說文新證">季旭昇《說文新證》 p316</ref> Compare the oracle bone script form of [[亟]].
* Xu Shen: {{Han compound|ls=ic|一|冓|t1=one|abb2=yes}} – to catch two fish at once.<ref>[https://www.zdic.net/hans/%E5%86%8D Shuowen Jiezi]</ref>
* {{Han compound|一|冓|ls=ic|t2=the shape of a basket repeatedly woven from bamboo}}. It signifies the concept of repeating something that was once done, conveying the meaning of "again."<ref>Digital Shinjigen 2017</ref>

