===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# [[again]]; [[once again]]; a [[second]] time; [[re-]]
#: {{zh-co|再 玩|play '''again'''}}
#: {{zh-co|一 拖 再 拖|to put off again '''and again'''}}
#: {{zh-x|我 再 說 一 遍。|I will say once '''again'''.}}
#: {{zh-x|後來 我 再 也 沒 見 過 他 了。|Afterwards I have never seen him again.}}
#* {{zh-x|燕子 去 了，有 再 來 的 時候；楊柳 枯 了，有 再 青 的 時候；桃花 謝 了，有 再 開 的 時候。|Gone are the swallows, still there's a time they'll come '''again'''. Wilted are the willows, still there's a time they'll be green '''again'''. Withered are the peach blossoms, still there's a time they'll bloom '''again'''.|ref='''1922''', {{w|Zhu Ziqing}}, {{lang|zh|[[s:zh:匆匆|匆匆]]}} "Hurrily"}}
# {{n-g|Used to indicate a continuing situation in conditional or suppositional clauses}}
#: {{zh-x|再 不 出發，我們 就 會 趕不上 火車 了。|If we don't leave now, we're going to miss the train.}}
# [[more]]; [[-er]]
#: {{zh-x|再 快 一點|faster}}
#: {{zh-x|再 大聲{seng1} 啲 得 唔 得 呀？|Louder please.|C}}
#: {{zh-x|小 得{de} 不能 再 小 的 芝麻小事|a trivial matter that cannot be more trivial}}
# {{n-g|Used with {{zh-l|也}} and followed by a negative expression}}; [[no matter]] how...[[still]] (not)
#: {{zh-x|你 再 努力 也 不會 成功。|No matter how hard you work, you will not succeed.}}
#: {{zh-x|有了 這 件 棉衣，再 冷 的 天 我 也 不 怕 了。|}}
# [[then]]; [[only]] then
#: {{zh-x|我們 吃 過 飯 再 回去 吧。|We shall eat before returning.}}
#: {{zh-co|到時 再 算|We'll see when the time comes.|C}}
# [[in addition]]; [[on top of that]]
# {{lb|zh|literary}} [[twice]]
#* {{zh-x|^季-文 ^子 三思.而.後行。子 聞 之，曰：「再，斯 可 矣。」|Ji Wen thought thrice, and then acted. When the Master was informed of it, he said, "'''Twice''' may do."|ref=Analects}}
#* {{zh-x|^秦 ^趙 五 戰，^秦 再 勝 而 ^趙 三 勝。|Qin and Zhao fought five battles against each other; Qin won '''twice''' while Zhao won three times.|ref=Shiji}}
# {{lb|zh|literary}} to [[appear]] again
#: {{zh-co|青春 不再|One’s youth never returns.}}
#* {{zh-x|嗚呼！勝地 不常，盛筵 難 再；^蘭亭 已 矣，^梓澤 丘墟。||ref={{lw|zh|王勃}} ({{w|Wang Bo (poet)|Wang Bo}}), {{lang|zh|[[s:zh:滕王閣序|滕王閣序]]}}|CL}}
# {{surname|zh}}

====Usage notes====
In Old Chinese, {{och-l|再}} strictly meant "twice" and not "again". The "second time" sense developed around the [[Tang]] dynasty.

{{zh-l|再}} is used for something that has not happened, while {{zh-l|又}} is used for something that already happened.

